sql:
SELECT AVG(confidence) AS average_confidence, MAX(fit_rating) AS max_fit_rating
FROM size_recommendations
WHERE item_id = 1;

SELECT item_id, AVG(fit_rating) AS average_fit_rating
FROM fit_preferences
GROUP BY item_id;

external_knowledge:
Highly Recommended: max_recommendation_confidence >= 0.8, review_count > 0; 
Recommended: max_recommendation_confidence < 0.8, review_count > 0; 
No Reviews: review_count = 0; 
Excellent: avg_rating >= 4; 
Good: 3 <= avg_rating < 4; 
Needs Improvement: avg_rating < 3; 
Not Rated: review_count = 0.

External knowledge:
- "complete order history" implies a comprehensive overview of past orders for each user;
- "fit preferences" refers to the user's preferred fit type and value for each item;
- "size recommendations" are personalized suggestions for each user based on their fit preferences;
- "cumulative spending" refers to the total amount spent by each user over time, calculated by summing their order amounts in chronological order.
